Hi Emil,

As you know from my last email, we were preparing a few huge features and new things, and today, we’re thrilled to unveil *two massive updates* that will transform how you create and interact with AI on Straico. Plus, we’ve got an exciting contest and a sneak peek at what’s coming next!

*🎉 Introducing the New Chatbar & Creations Gallery*

*A Smarter, More Powerful Chatbar*

Your workflow (and experience in Straico) just got a major upgrade! The new chat interface puts *full control right where you work* , with:
✅ *Instant context switching* and *LLM combos* tailored to your needs.
✅ *Toggle Reasoning* & *Web Browsing* on or off with ease.
✅ *Seamless multimedia generation* : images, videos, and audio. With intuitive selectors and an optional *Prompt Optimizer* for richer outputs.

We’ve also expanded our multimedia model lineup, bringing you cutting-edge tools like:

* *Text-to-Image* : Bagel, FLUX.1, Google Imagen 4, Ideogram V3, and more.
* *Image-to-Video* : Google Veo 2, Kling 2.1 Pro, Runway Gen-3 & Gen-4.
* *Text-to-Speech* : OpenAI and ElevenLabs.

From text to stunning media *just a few clicks away!*
I have the feeling that our Showcase channel in the Discord community ( https://discord.gg/straico-community-1118690015443161130 ) will have even more awesome creations quite soon!

*🖼️ Your Creations Gallery & Public Inspiration Feed*

The new *Creations Gallery* keeps all your generated media organized and easy to revisit. Need inspiration? Dive into our *Public Inspiration Feed* to spark your creativity.

*🛠️ Straico API Gets a Power-Up!*

And of course we are not forgetting our power users, automation experts and developers!

The Straico API is now *more powerful and versatile than ever* , unlocking new ways to build, create, and innovate. Here’s what’s new:
🎨 *Top-tier image models* (GPT Image 1, Google Imagen 4, FLUX.1, and more).
🎬 *Image-to-video* with Kling 2.1, Google Veo 2, and Runway Gen-3/4.
🗣️ *Text-to-speech* with ElevenLabs and OpenAI voices.

Ready to integrate? Check out the full API docs here ( https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/5900072/2s9YyzddrR ).

